reviews.review_text:
bread crumb You can certainly hear why Brent was the answer.  The organ, a little creamier here than he would evolve to, adds a texture that just wasn't a part of the mix with Keith's plinking about.  Thinking about the context of the late '70s, when punk and new wave were at the cutting edge, the band is simply more agressive in a way that has not been evidenced since 1971.

Another great audience recording.  Just like being there.
